content: I can't trust half of the answers for tachycardic rhythms.

A great app to use to study and learn heart rhythms. Some minor flaws however, such as missing some rhythms including supraventricular tachycardia, sinus pause, sinus arrest, wandering pacemaker... Also had some flaws where the app identified a rhythm multiple times as atrial tachycardia, yet in the description the criteria for atrial tachycardia did not meet the rhythm presented. Nevertheless, a great study tool for just a dollar. I would give 3.5 stars if I could.
